%section.hero
  .row
    .large-4.medium-4.columns.about-box
      .black-box
        %h3{:color => "white"}
          %font{:color => "#FF9C5B"}
            Sign Up.
            %small
              %font{:color => "#FAD089"} It's Free
        = form_for @user do |f|
          = f.text_field :full_name, placeholder: "Full Name"
          = f.email_field :email, placeholder: "Email address"
          = f.password_field :password, placeholder: "Password"
          = f.submit "Sign me up!", class: "button"
%section.container
  .row.title
    .small-12.column
      %h6 This is a practice project.
  .row
    .large-12.column
      %p My little album allow users to upload photos. The photos will remain private unless set otherwise. The photos will be categorized by date.
      %p New parents who wishes to save each and every memory with their kid need not worry about running out of space on their phone, overwhelming their Facebook/Instagram pages with baby photos, having photos on multiple devices and most importantly losing the photos and the memories/stories behind them.
      %p
        Checkout
        %a{:href => "https://www.gotealeaf.com/"} Tealeaf Academy
        to learn how to build robust and production quality applications using Ruby on Rails.
      %a.button{:href => "https://github.com/vajradog/mylittlealbum"} Source Code: Ideas/Contributions are welcome